Frank WEATHERSBEE, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES, Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. January 25, 1930. No. 5610. Charles D. Russell, of Savannah, Ga. (Russell & Herzog, of Savannah, Ga., on the brief), for appellant. Charles L. Redding, U. S. Atty., of Savannah, Ga. (Harry M. Wilson, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Savannah, Ga., on the brief), for the United States.

Before BRYAN and FOSTER, Circuit Judges, and GRUBB, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment in the above numbered and entitled cause is affirmed.
